  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Scottish Ebola riposte  Lubero DRC</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aim to reduce the risk of Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) contamination in South Lubero, North Kivu, DRC through community engagement and WASH.  Affected communities are mobilized to consult and collaborate with Ebola response teams and reduce resistance. Improved Wash infrastructure, access to hygiene materials and hygiene promotion lead to good and consistently applied Wash practices and help prevent human to human transmission of EVD</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">By the end of the project implementation period, people living in the affected areas will benefit from project&apos;s outcomes to accept and collaborate with the reposte team and minimize the resistance. wash facilities infrastructures will be improved to offer  appropriate and fair hygienic environment to prevent form Ebola risk contamination. People in the communities will be enable with communication skills and wash technic around EVD to increase their resilience.</narrative>
  </description>
